    "Obrix"
  ],
  "description": "One electrical brick — the fundamental building block of an electrical storm, isolated and studied. Noise src1 + Triangle src2 (srcMix=0.3 — the triangle gives the brick a tonal center, like the frequency signature of a specific lightning formation). proc1=BP (2100 Hz, reso=0.72) sculpts the electrical character; proc2=LP (6000 Hz) protects the upper atmosphere. gestureMode=3 (Tide/Surge), flashTrigger=0.7. aggression=0.45 — meditative but with real electrical presence. Long release (1.2s) for atmospheric sustain. The FLASH gesture here fires as a considered event, not a storm. LFO->FilterCutoff (0.28 Hz), Env->FilterReso (reso opens on attack), Velocity->Volume, Aftertouch->Pan. CHARACTER 0.32, MOVEMENT 0.38.",
